! : prototype_OfficeMedium_template.tmpl,v 1.2 2011/02/19 17:45:44 d3l143 Exp Inappropriate ioctl for device : prototype_OfficeMedium_template.tmpl,v Inappropriate ioctl for device Revision 1.2  2011/02/19 17:45:44  d3l143
! change path for gtp, opaque and window library.
!
! Revision 1.1  2011/02/16 17:41:44  d3l143
! Initial revision
!
!
! ------------------------------------------------------------------
! Sep 18-21, 2013: Adding back the comments from V6 templates to the automatic upgraded V8 templates.
!                  Moving the comments out of the objects.
!                  Commenting out [design_wetbulb] which was defined but not used in Midrise, 3 offices and Warehouse.
! 01. February 5, 2013: (2) change the gtp path to the new folder for state ana;ysis and (2) allow both TMY2 and TMY3 epw files
!
!
! This input file was originally created as DOE Commercial Building Benchmark V 2.0
! and is modified in supporting ASHRAE SSPC 90.1 30% Project
! List of changes made to the DOE Commercial Building Benchmark V 2.0
! 1. Change the floor-to-ceiling height from 10 ft to 9ft and add 4-ft high above-ceiling plenum for each floor as return air plenum.
! 2. Change the window dimensions to match the same 33% WWR.
! 3. Add ground temperature from the slab-on-grade runs.
! 4. Change one packaged unitary air conditioner serving the whole building to one unit per floor.
! 5. Seasonal supply air temperature reset is deleted.
! 6. Infiltration schedule is changed to 25% of peak infiltration rate when fan is on and 100% of peak infiltration rate when fan is off
! 7. Infiltration rate is changed based on PNNL's study and 90.1 committee's input
! 8. Changed the occupancy densities based on Standard 62.1-2004 and minimum OA rate based on Standard 62-1999 for 90.1-2004 models.
! 10.Revised geometry deleting the AutoCreateOther surfaces and replaced it with the unenteredOtherZoneSurface option.
! 11. Added exterior lighting. (source: Std. 189 TSD)
! 12. Add elevator. (source: Commercial Building Benchmark V1.0-3.0)
! 13. Zone Sizing: change zone cooling design supply air temperature from 14 deg.to 12.8 to match actual supply air temperature (for all zones)
! 14. System Sizing:
!     a. Changed Central heating coil design supply air temp from 16.7 to 12.8 (to match CC)
!     b. Changed system sizing option from NONCOINCIDENT to COINCIDENT
! 15. Changed both cool and heat supply air temperature schedule from 13 deg. to 12.8 deg
!     (Cool-Supply-Air-Temp-Sch; Heat-Supply-Air-Temp-Sch)
! 16. Changed the economizer control by deleting the low temperature limit and by using the differential drybulb control.
!     (ALL OBJECTS IN CLASS: CONTROLLER:OUTSIDE AIR)
! 17. Minimum OA Schedule and Damper Control:
! a. Added a new minimum outside air schedule "MinOA_MotorizedDamper_Sched" and the new schedule
!          sets to shut off minimum OA air damper when the fan is on at 6 am for morning start up in Zone 4-8.
! b. Kept the same "MinOA_Sched" schedule for Min_OA in Zone 1-3 since gravity damper is allowed in Zone 1-3 by the Standard 90.1.
! 18. Changed the variable speed fan curve coefficient to match the fan static pressure reset control based on the research study
!     from the Advanced Variable Air Volume System Design Guide.
!     (ALL OBJECTS IN CLASS: FAN:SIMPLE:VARIABLEVOLUME)
! 19. Changed the heating and cooling t-stat schedule during moring warm up or cool down hours
!     (HTGSETP_SCH;CLGSETP_SCH)
! 20. Changed Sizing Parameters: Sizing Factor=1.0; TimeSteps=8
! 21. Changed the VAV terminal box damper heating action from Reserve Action to Normal to meet 90.1 requirement.
!     (ALL OBJECTS IN CLASS: SINGLE DUCT:VAV:REHEAT)
! 22. Deleted constructions and added the envelope library reference
! 23. Changed the Exterior lighting schedule to ALWAYS ON in the exterior lights object.  Exterior lighting control will be based on astronomical clock
!     (Object:ExteriorLights).
! 24. Changed the service hot water temperature setpoint from 140F (60C) to 120F (48.9C).
! 25. add a variable "[NoEconomizer]"
! 26. August 12, 2009:  checked the "view factor to ground" and "autocalculate" used for all.  No changes are made.
! 27. August 21, 2009: implement Addendum X
!                      change lighting density from 10.764 W/m2 --> 10.548 w/m2 with a 0.216 W/m2 reduction
! 28. August 25, 2009: adding PI.Oct09 cases in the PARM
!     Notice that there is exterior lighting change after the Jun09 PI runs.
!                 specifically for 2004/2007 changed from 14913 --> 14383 (75)
!                              for PI cases  changed from 8702  --> 8099  (603)
!                                                         (6211)    (6739) less ext lgt for PI.Oct09 than PI.Jun09 after the change
! 29. September 15, 2009: revise the implementation of addendum X (15 out of 18 zones are affected)
!                         change lighting density from 10.765 W/m2 --> 10.559 w/m2 with a 0.2056 W/m2 reduction
! 30. November 5, 2009: standardize the LPD by
!                     (a) specifyed 1 LPD parm variable in the PARM excel file
!                     (b) replaced the hard coded Watts/Area in 15 zones (out of 18 zones) in this template with the PARM LPD variable LPD_office
! 31. December 28, 2009: Addendum c and q - Vestibule requriement
!      (a) Door infiltration schduecle (INFIL_Door_Opening_SCH) has been added.
!      (b) Door infiltration (ZoneInfiltration) has been added to Perimeter_bot_ZN_1.
!      (c) Door infiltration value (door_infil) and fraction for off-peak hour (frac_ofpk) are inputted in the parm file.
! 32. February 4, 2010: Upgrade from V3.0 to 4.0
! 33. June 2, 2010
!     replace "MinOA_Motorized_Damper_Sched" with [MinOA_MotorizedDamper_Sched] for the 3 Controller:OutdoorAir objects.
!     a parm variable "MinOA_MotorizedDamper_Sched" is added in the parm accordingly
! 34. added a monthly indoor temp.
!
! 25. September 28, 2010: Implemented Addendum BS-CS for receptacles. This addendum modifies building equipment schedule for PI and Determination cases.
! 26. October 11, 2010: Change the path of slab gtp
! 27. December 13, 2010: modified elevator motor and added elevator fan/lighting. PARM variable BLDG_ELEVATORS_LIGHTS_FAN_SCH and BLDG_ELEVATORS_LIGHTS_FAN_POWER ARE added for Addendum DF.
! 28. January 31,  2011: (1) (addendum BS_CS)
!                             used parm variable "BLDG_QUIP_SCH" which has two values "BLDG_EQUIP_SCH_BASE" & "BLDG_EQUIP_SCH_ADV".
!                             removed the standard related IF condition by re-define to "BLDG_EQUIP_SCH_BASE" & "BLDG_EQUIP_SCH_ADV".
!                             replaced 15 "BLDG_QUIP_SCH" with parm variables
!                        (2)  defined a parm "addendum_cd" ro replace those IF condition in exterior lights objects associated with standard.
! 29. Thursday, June 02, 2011 Implement ERV to PACU_VAV_BOT, PACU_VAV_MID, and PACU_VAV_TOP to meet 189.1-2009 requirements.
! 30. Friday, August 03, 2012: optimum start function for whole building is implemented as choices for IECC and 90.1 models through added schedules and HtgSetP_Sch ClgSetP_Sch variables.
! 31. Monday, August 13, 2012: Added lighting schedule sets for all standards (LTG_SET_STD2004)
! 32. more revision/verification on SWH Model Enhancement on August 15, 2012
! 33. Sep 25, 2012: Added " DX_TwoSpeedObject_from_VAV" to mark the two Speed DX Coil which will not be overwritten by the sizing script
! 34. May 1, 2013: crrect addendum cd implenetation by changing the reduction from 0.3 to 0.7
!
!-Generator IDFEditor 1.31
!-Option SortedOrder
!-NOTE: All comments with '!-' are ignored by the IDFEditor and are generated automatically.
!-      Use '!' comments if they need to be retained when using the IDFEditor.
!-   ===========  ALL OBJECTS IN CLASS: VERSION ===========
